The paper focuses on analyzing the demographics of news spreaders in social media, which falls under the categories of social media analysis and information retrieval. Therefore, cs.SI and cs.SOC are the most likely categories. Additionally, the paper also discusses the content shared and the audience reached, which could fall under the categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). Finally, the paper mentions personalized news digests, which could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
